cs.NI, cs.RO, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM

This paper discusses the challenges and solutions for wireless communication with UAVs, which involves networking, control systems, information theory, signal processing, and multimedia. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also covers the use of UAVs as aerial base stations, which falls under the sub-category cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also discusses channel modeling and optimization, which are related to cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper mentions the use of UAVs for real-time search and rescue, which involves multimedia processing and falls under the sub-category cs.MM (Multimedia).
